body:
@shahasim Thanks for the stacktrace.

> expect mlflow server to handle authentication with the google cloud storage bucket using the service account set by the env

No, it doesn't by default. I think https://www.mlflow.org/docs/latest/tracking.html#scenario-5-mlflow-tracking-server-enabled-with-proxied-artifact-storage-access can help. Here's an example that demonstrates how to use the proxy server feature: https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/tree/master/examples/mlflow_artifacts

@harupy thank you for the feedback. I'll investigate this options and get back to you.

I am trying to simplify the use of mlflow for my team, so essentially when they add `mlflow.evaluate()` or `mlflow.log_artifact()` to their pipelines they don't have to explicitly define `os.environ['GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS'] = '/Users/myname/Documents/json_serv.json'`.. 

I'll check the scenario 5 and associated example and provide my feedback... many thanks :)
